OL,3,C"I'm not just angry. I'm broken by
OL,4,Cthis."
OL,6,FHe added: "This is a man convicted of
OL,7,Fbeing involved in the murder of 22
OL,8,Finnocent people, including children.
OL,9,FHow is it remotely acceptable that he
OL,10,Fhas access to anything that could pose
OL,11,Fa danger ` to staff, to other inmates,
OL,12,For to the principles of justice itself?
OL,14,F"I was led to believe that people like
OL,15,Fhim ` mass murderers, terrorists `
OL,16,Fwould face a regime of strict control
OL,17,Fand zero comfort. I was told justice
OL,18,Fwould be served. What I see now is not
OL,19,Fjustice. It's a shameful lack of
OL,20,Faccountability and basic prison
OL,21,Fsecurity.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
